AB  - Abid talks about war, media, and war journalism in Afghan Jihad. War and media are intimately linked; both are waged campaigns and, as a more cynical worldview would contend, both are forms of communication. Public opinion about war is profoundly affected by how news about war is delivered. The parameters of war and the battlefield it is fought in, along with the stated goals, explicit or implicit, are shaped by media in its different forms. From organized and organizing bodies of knowledge that describe and define rules of engagement and set goals, to distinguishing between "allies" and "enemies," the duality between war and the plain that it is communicated in is of immense importance to hostile parties. The form and medium of communication (media) itself is not a mere question of technological resourcefulness but a socially and culturally sensitive process informed by contextual particularities.
